---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import houseImage from "../assets/images/house.jpg";

const experienceInYears = new Date().getFullYear() - 2020;
const currentYear = new Date().getFullYear();
---

<BaseLayout title="nbr.haus">
  <header class="page-header">
    <img class="house-image" src={houseImage.src} alt="House" />
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>About</h2>
    <p>
      Software Engineer with {experienceInYears} years of experience building frontend architectures and design systems. Currently seeking new opportunities starting February 2026.
    </p>

    <p>Born in 1984, based in Landshut, Germany. Outside of code, I enjoy hiking, photography, reading and music.</p>

    <h2>Work</h2>
    <h3>DealerCenter Digital — Software Engineer (2020-{currentYear})</h3>
    <p>
      Led major architectural migrations across a mature Electron application serving bike retailers. Designed and implemented a <strong>comprehensive 10-variant color system</strong> with <strong>Figma integration</strong>, affecting the entire codebase. Migrated the application from <strong>legacy Redux to Redux Toolkit</strong> and championed <strong>TanStack Query adoption</strong> with comprehensive <strong>code guidelines and best practices documentation</strong>. Built BikeCenter's <strong>custom design system from scratch</strong> using React, TypeScript, and SCSS. Completely rebuilt a Vendure storefront from a <strong>Remix template to TanStack Start/Router</strong> with TanStack Form, GraphQL, and Tailwind CSS.
    </p>
    <p>
      Established <strong>technical standards</strong> and <strong>coding conventions</strong> across the team, including <strong>translation guidelines</strong>, <strong>BEM naming conventions</strong>, and <strong>TypeScript best practices</strong>. <strong>Mentored junior developers</strong> through pair programming and code reviews, creating extensive documentation for knowledge transfer. Coordinated cross-functional teams as <strong>technical hub</strong> between management, backend, and frontend, facilitating communication and ensuring alignment on architectural decisions.
    </p>

    <h3>diva-e — Junior Frontend Developer (2020)</h3>
    <p>
      Worked on BayWa's e-commerce platform at a digital agency. Built features with their design system, <strong>created documentation for an undocumented internal framework</strong>, and developed an internal Instagram-like tool using React, GraphQL, and Apollo. Started during COVID-19, worked primarily remote while onboarding independently.
    </p>

    <h3>Campudus — Intern (2019-2020)</h3>
    <p>
      Built a fullstack accessories ordering application from scratch (design, architecture, backend, frontend) during a 3-month internship at DealerCenter Digital's sister company.
    </p>

    <h2>Projects</h2>
    <h3>Black Atom — <a href="https://black-atom.industries">black-atom.industries</a></h3>
    <p>
      Open-source theming system with 27+ themes across 6 platforms (Neovim, Zed, Ghostty, WezTerm, Tmux, and more). Built with an <strong>adapter pattern</strong> for consistent theme generation from a central source using <strong>OKLCH color space</strong>. Maintained with focus on developer experience and cross-platform consistency.
    </p>

    <h2>Stack</h2>
    <p>
      React, TypeScript, GraphQL, Tailwind CSS, TanStack (Router/Query/Form), ShadCN, SCSS, Node.js, Electron, Redux Toolkit
    </p>
    <p>
      Currently exploring: Databases, Authentication systems, Docker
    </p>

    <h2>Tools</h2>
    <p>
      <a href="https://github.com/nikbrunner/vin">Neovim</a>, <a href="https://zed.dev">Zed</a>, <a href="https://wezfurlong.org/wezterm/">Wezterm</a>, TMUX, VSCode, WebStorm
    </p>
    <p>
      Passionate about workflow optimization with <a href="https://github.com/nikbrunner/dots">extensive dotfiles</a> featuring custom scripts, unified configuration management, and cross-platform tooling.
    </p>

    <h2>Connect</h2>
    <p>
      <a href="https://www.github.com/nikbrunner">GitHub</a> · <a href="mailto:nbr.haus.persuader046@passmail.com">Email (Alias)</a> · <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nbru/">LinkedIn</a>
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    position: relative;

    &:after {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      top: 0;
      left: 0;
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      background-color: var(--fg-accent);
      opacity: 0.05;
    }
  }

  .house-image {
    width: 100%;
    height: 40vh;
    object-fit: cover;
    display: block;
  }
</style>
